<br>
<br>
As I said before, I was raised as a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;hard scientist,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> with a strong background in mathematics, physics and astronomy, and when I was younger I viewed social science with disdain.  However, as my education broadened, and I learned more about the various social sciences, I came recognize their power and application.  The scientific method is a powerful one, and it can be applied to questions of human behavior.<br>
<br>
I recommend you keep a more open mind, and not dismiss something simply because it is unfamiliar or does not fit your world view.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ...OBVIOUS FACT...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->If you had some exposure to social science, you would be aware that there are few if any <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;obvious facts&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> anywhere when humans are involved.  In practice, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;fact&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> often turn out to be shared assumptions, and labelling something as being <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;obvious&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is nothing more than an attempt to bully people into agreement.  That is, since it is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;obvious,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> anyone who disagrees must be a moron.  And this is exactly what you are suggesting.  Hardly a refutation of my points.<br>
<br>
The word <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;obvious&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has no explanatory value whatsover, nor does it convince any but the timid.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ...are talking out of their rears, and let's face it, we all know it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Trying to bully or insult me will get you nowhere, as you should know if you read this forum.  Claiming that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;everyone knows&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is also an empty argument.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If you're trying to get into stereotypical 'perfect' groups, you're competing against every other non-Holy Trinity class for that one coveted spot... so don't bother, it's a waste of your time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Exactly.  Difficulty in getting a spot in a group style that does not favor <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> does not by itself entail the inferiority of that class.  Nor does the popularity of that style prove that it is objectively the best or only viable style.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So find yourself a partner, make yourself a group, make it as unorthadox as possible, you'd be surprised.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Exactly.  Behave <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>differently</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, and you will get <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>different</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> results.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If this is the case then I bet you level slow as piss cause you sure as hell arent playing in any zones where you get good xp.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Currently having a grand old time in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Fungus Grove</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, with a fair number of other 60+ players who enjoy having steady experience.  Sometimes I get an AOE group there, and pull two or three mushroom patches at once.  While I may not be getting absolutely the best experience in the game, I start exping within 5 minutes of logging in, and continue to exp until the call comes to raid.  I don't worry about camp checks, because I can apply my grouping strategy in a variety of places.  People send me tells asking me if I can join in gaining experience.<br>
<br>
Some theoretical maximum of experience gained per hour means nothing if you are LFG, or if the camp is not available.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Mages = suck, sorry, thats just the way it is...the fact is mages = suck, end of story...I know most of you dont wanna hear it &amp; would rather just stick your head in the sand, but its just fact.  Mages SUCK - think i'll just reiterate that again for those of you that missed it above...everything a group needs...well mages aint got it.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Labelling your opinions as facts does not make them so.  Insults and bullying mean nothing.  Repeating your opinions is no argument at all.  You convince no one.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So then you are not denying that if you want to get into a &quot;classic group&quot; which btw is the most common, you will have better luck with a few classes other than a mage.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I think I just said that.  However, my response is that there are other group styles, and by acting differently, a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> need not suffer.  Stereotyped play is not the only possibility.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Right now I think your arguing for arguments sake, and ignoring the initial point that he said that he has trouble getting into a group after level 50. I'd hate to give young mages the wrong idea about the problems they will face because you expect other mages to always be a group leader like you.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I am arguing because I feel strongly that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> shortchange themselves if they accept stereotyped groups as being the only legitimate group form.  I am suggesting that there is an alternative to stereotyped groups.  I would hate it if young <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> let stereotypes dictate their choices, and conclude that they suck.<br>
<br>
If all you want are stereotyped classic groups, then you deserve your self imposed exile.  If you chose to live inside a prison of your own perceptions and others, and I cannot convince you otherwise, then I have no choice but to leave you to rot there, even though the bars are solely in your mind.  For those who are brave enough to risk going against the crowd, I assure you the rewards are worth it.<br>
<br>
Lastly, I am a strong and active advocate of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Maigician Class Balance</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, so no one should accuse me of believing that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magicians</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have no problems.  I do however believe that they are less than many others, and that alternatives exist to classic groups.<br>
