<br>
There are also several ways to get peoples attention when LFG and /ooc is the most pathetic way.<br>
<br>
Try this a couple weeks and see how it goes.<br>
<br>
Enter a zone like Seb.<br>
/who enc(or any class)<br>
/tell enc Hey ENC_Name_Here!!  Hi I'm looking to have some fun and get some experience.  Send me a tell if a spot opens up in your group.  That cool?<br>
Ench_name_Here tells you.  Sure, Okay, or. Hey we have a spot opening in 5 minutes.  can you make it to NG?<br>
<br>
Add the people that are friendly and invited you to group to your friends list.  then you can /who all friends. and send them a tell saying you had fun in their group the other day and if a spot opens you'd enjoy grouping with them.<br>
<br>
Go ahead and turn /lfg on<br>
<br>
/who LFG - <br>
/tell LFG_01 hey! want to Duo with me while we LFG?  <br>
LFG_01 telss you &quot;Sure&quot;<br>
/invite LFG_01, /invite LFG_02<br>
<br>
/who all LFG can help too.<br>
<br>
I may not recieve tells from people asking me to group all the time but it does happen.  And when I've never gotten a rude response from someone I've sent a request to.<br>
<br>
Then ten minutes later you may recieve a tell.<br>
Nice_Guy_010 tells you &quot;Hey buddy you still LFG?&quot;<br>
/reply Sorry Nice Guy but we'll have to group next time.  Just got invited to AE group!!!  Good luck tonight!<br>
<br>
edit* just and addition.  I got invited to fill the 6th spot consiting of the following group in Seb.<br>
<br>
War<br>
War<br>
Rog<br>
Cle<br>
Wiz<br>
<br>
Thanks go out to the Spirit Guardians on Saryrn.  We then proceeded to lower zone out trying to root adds and keep our heads above the water.  <br>
<br>
Not everyone out there is out to keep the mages down.<br>
